SIX suspects were planning to commit robbery in their kasi.But residents tipped off police before the plan was carried out on Friday.Four of the six men were arrested on the same day, while two managed to flee when cops pounced on them in Umlazi G section.They were found in possession of two home-made guns with two live rounds of ammunition.KZN cops spokesman Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane confirmed the arrests.He said: &ldquo;The suspects will be profiled to check if they are not linked to any other robberies committed in Umlazi and the surrounding areas.&rdquo; He said the suspects, believed to be in their 20s, will appear in the Umlazi Magistrates Court today for possession of unlicensed firearms and ammunition. &ldquo;Two bags of dagga, a computer screen and a speaker were also found abandoned in one of the houses the suspects were spotted at,&rdquo; added Zwane.Meanwhile, Zwane said Umlazi cops bust a man (30) who tried to hijack a truck driver at gunpoint along Prince Mcwayizeni Drive near Glebelands Hostel in Umlazi.&ldquo;Police were given a description of the suspect and quickly traced him. When police approached him, he fled into the hostel and police gave chase. The suspect was eventually arrested. He was found in possession of a 9mm pistol with ammunition,&rdquo; said Zwane.The suspect is expected to appear in court today.